nodes.title: Resolution note
widgets_values:
### Automatic scaling and resolution calculation The initial image will be scaled on optimized math targeting a WAN 2.2 VAE (div16) resolution. Aspect will be calculated automatically and the video resolution will be set to the nearest possible match with the megapixel count. | Stage | Target MP | Quality | Use case | |---:|---:|---:|---| | 1 | 0.25 | Fast Preview
~ 360p| Motion/physics tests. | | 2 | 0.40 | SD
~ 480p| "Sweet spot" for speed. | | 3 | 0.60 | SD+
~ 576p| Optimal for mobile-first content. | | 4 | 0.85 | HD
~ 720p| Very stable, crisp details. | | 5 | 1.05 | HD+
~ 768p| Maximum stability for Image-to-Video. | | 6 | 1.30 | HQ
~ 900p| High detail, very slow (Requires high VRAM). | | 7 | 2.07 | FHD
~ 1080p| Production grade detail, extreme slow (Requires very high VRAM). |

nodes.title: Settiings and features
widgets_values:
## BASIC settings and features | Setting | Default / Example | Description | |---|---:|---| | **VAE** | same as WAN 2.1 | Still using the same VAE as WAN 2.1. | | **CLIP** | standard encoder | Use your preferred standard CLIP text encoder. No CLIP Vision H ‚Äî not trained/implemented in WAN 2.2 and weights are disabled. | | **CLIP device** | "cpu" or "default" | CLIP can be offloaded to CPU for VRAM savings ‚Üí device = "cpu". If VRAM is sufficient, use device = "default" for faster inference. | | **Checkpoint** | Safetensors/GGUf |Choose the type of Checkpoint to use. Wan 2.2 uses a different diffusion model for the first steps (high noise) vs the last steps (low noise). You can ether use safetensors or gguf.| | **LoRAs** | none | Try without LoRA first for a baseline. Add LoRAs to your liking for stylistic/behavioral tweaks. | | **Seed** | -1 | -1 ‚Üí random outcome every run. Set a specific seed to reproduce the same outcome. | | **FPS** | 16 | Frames per second for videos. Use 24 for faster motion/shorter videos. | | **Frames** | 49‚Äì113 | Total frames determine video length. Examples: 3s=49, 4s=65, 5s=81, 6s=97, 7s=113. Math: (Seconds * 16) + 1 = total frames. | | **Feature switch** | off/on | Enable features you want to use. | | **CRF** | 30 | Video compression level. 30 is near-lossless (AV1). | | **Steps total** | 4 | Total steps - node handles step math. More steps ‚Üí higher quality but longer generation. Use even numbers. | | **Step Refiner** | 2 | Default 2 (50% of 4). Change to test different swap behavior. | | **CFG** | 1.0 | Controls prompt adherence. Use 1-1.5. 1 disables/ignores the negative prompt. 1.0 is needed for speed-up's like 4/8-step models/LoRAs | | **Sigma Shift** | 5 | Default 5. Adjust and test; WAN 2.2 valid in range 5‚Äì8. | | **Video resolution** | R2# | Scale to selected MP with automatic calculations. Affects sampling time, VRAM and RAM usage. | | **Upscale** | 2x | Final resolution = 2 √ó start resolution while maintaining aspect ratio. No morph; aspect-correct to optimal WAN resolution. | | **Positive prompt** | none | Write your positive prompt!
1) Brief description of the setting/appearance
2) Actions, motions, story
3) Camera composition
CFG 1 normally disables/ignores the negative prompt! NAG effectively enables negative prompting on CFG 1.| | **Negative prompt** | none | Write what you would like to exclude. Works only if CFG > 1 or NAG is enabled | | **NAG** | off | This will use your negative condition and concat it with the standard WAN AI negative prompt for convenience.
If you do not want this, just disable the standard negative node.
‚ö†Ô∏èNAG needs a lot of VRAM, so if you do not need this. Just let it be disabled. | | **FLF2V** | off | This enables the usage of a "First-Last-Frame to video". The video will start with the 1st frame and end with the last frame. Both must be set/uploaded. | | **Interpolation** | off | This will interpolate your video to double fps at the end. Interpolated FPS = 2 √ó FPS. | | **Watermark** | off | Here you can set a watermark image and calibrate the settings to your liking. | | **Color match** | 0.5 | This will try to match the color from the initial image to the samples. The color match algorithms default is set by default to '0.5'. Feel free to test other strength. | | **MiniMeme** | off | This will create a mini gif from your video down scaled by 5 for meme's or discord. |
Just the standard WAN 2.2 negatives. Leave as is.
